-- Target's view drags down other retailers
-- 
-- Tue Sep 25, 2007 9:03am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/25/us-before-the-bell-targets-idUSL2577259520070925

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Target ( TGT.N ) and its rivals fell before the opening bell on Tuesday, a day after the discount department store chain said it sees sales at stores open at least a year well below its prior forecast. 

 Target shares fell 4.2 percent to $61.60 before the opening bell. Shares of Wal-Mart Stores Inc ( WMT.N ) fell 1.4 percent to $43.35 and shares of Kohl's Corp ( KSS.N ) lost 2.2 percent to $57.70.